    "Li et al. (2021) experimentally confirmed in vitro resistance for some examples of Pseudomonas aeruginosa AMR genes predicted by their model in cases where direct sequence similarity methods would have failed due to low nucleotide identity with existing databases.",
    "A class of ML-based methods is devoted to identifying viruses or viral fragments from metagenomic data, including methods with a specific focus on bacteriophages (Ho et al., 2023; Amgarten et al., 2018; Kieft et al., 2020; Auslander et al., 2020; Guo et al., 2021; Bai et al., 2022).",
    "The principle underpinning these methods is that fragments of a viral genome share more features with other viruses than they do with non-viral organisms present in the library.",
    "Subtle differences in nucleotide or k-mer frequency, or particular motifs might provide enough clues for a model to identify a viral read even when it is quite dissimilar to its nearest relative in reference databases.",
    "Other tools sub-categorise viral reads including to distinguish temperate phages from virulent phages (Wu et al., 2021)."
  ],
